  "notes": [
    "This proposal opened the Git-substrate lane without implementing adapters prematurely, then closed the first real-runtime adapter tranche explicitly.",
    "gix and sem are projected adapters, not authority surfaces.",
    "A first Git-substrate semantic example and realization payload now exist.",
    "Compatibility posture and realization workflow contract now exist for the first slice.",
    "A first Git-substrate realization runner now exists and emits normalized manifest/report artifacts.",
    "Runner-owned Git transform logic is now split into bounded gix and sem emitter artifacts.",
    "Real-runtime contracts for gix and sem now distinguish the completed first adapter tranche from the minimal proof path.",
